com.metreeca.back.virtuoso

Class Virtuoso

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.metreeca.back.sparql.Graph
      • com.metreeca.back.virtuoso.Virtuoso
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    AutoCloseable

    public final class Virtuoso
extends Graph
    Virtuoso graph store.

    Manages task execution on an Virtuoso repository.

    Warning / Be aware of the following issues with Virtuoso, which could affect custom SPARQL-based code:

    • aggregate count() is reported as an xsd:int value rather than csd:integer;
    • string literals in SPARQL code are parsed as RDF 1.0 plain string literals rather than RDF 1.1 xsd:string literals.

    • Constructor Detail

      • Virtuoso

        public Virtuoso(String url,
                String usr,
                String pwd,
                IRI dflt)
        Creates a Virtuoso graph.
        Parameters:
        url - the JDBC URL of a remote Virtuoso server (e.g. jdbc:virtuoso://localhost:1111/)
        usr - the username of the account on the remote Virtuoso server
        pwd - the password of the account on the remote Virtuoso server
        dflt - the IRI of the default graph for update operations on the remote Virtuoso server
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - if any argument is null
